def: To indicate, as by a symptom, some method of treatment contraryto that which the general tenor of the case would seem to require.Contraindicating symptoms must be observed. Harvey.
Having a single rib or strong nerve running upward from thebase; -- said of a leaf.
The thickness of the layer or body of pigment applied by thepainter to his canvas with especial reference to the juxtaposition ofdifferent colors and tints in forming a harmonious whole. Fairholt.
A cartilage or bone in front of the pubis in some amphibiansand other animals.
The office or jurisdiction of a patriarch; patriarchate. [R.]
A post-office clerk in charge of the nixies.
A large edible river fish (Erythrinus macrodon) of Guiana.
A kind of graduated breech sight for a small arm, or a cannon.
